Q. What are the reasons for data loss in Salesforce?
A. Data loss may cause due to following reasons:Changing data and date-time
Altering to percent,number and currency from other data types
Changing from multi-select picklist, checkbox, auto number to other types
Altering to multi-select picklist from any type except picklist
Changing to auto-number except from text
Changing from text-area to e-mail, phone, URL and text

Q. order of execution in salesforce.
Link for the order of execution:  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aQGfR1atq6Y

Here is an order of execution in salesforce

1)	The original record is loaded from the database.
2)	System Validation Rules.
3)	Before flow
4)	Executes all before triggers.
5)	Custom Validation rules.
6)	Executes duplicate rules.
7)	Saves the record to the database, but doesn’t commit yet.(record id will generated)
8)	Executes all after triggers.( In after trigger is creating new record then entire flow will be happen for the newly created record)
9)	Executes assignment rules.
10)	Executes auto-response rules.
11)	Executes workflow rules. If the record was updated with workflow field updates, fires before update triggers and after update triggers one more time (and only one more time), in addition to standard validations. Custom validation rules, flows, duplicate rules, processes, and escalation rules are not run again.
12)	Process builder and auto lunched flows. In process builder if we update field of the same record then it will execute from step4 (before tiggers) to step13(process builder) again. If the process builder or auto lunched flow update a field on the other record or create a new then it will execute from step 1 to step 17 for the new record. Commit and post commit  will not run for the newly created until the original record commit and post commit steps complete.
13)	Executes escalation rules.
14)	Executes entitlement rules.
15)	After flows.
16)	Rollup summery->if the parent record has rollup summary fields, then it will execute from step 1 to step 17 for the master record. Commit and post commit will not run for the master record until the original record commit and post commit steps complete.
17)	Executes Criteria Based Sharing evaluation.
18)	Commits all DML operations to the database.
19)	Executes post-commit logic, such as sending an email.

 


Q. in the order of the execution of the salesforce if we have any field update then what will be the flow.
A. If the record was updated with workflow field updates, fires before update triggers and after update triggers one more time (and only one more time), in addition to standard validations. Custom validation rules, flows, duplicate rules, processes, and escalation rules are not run again.

