Q. If there is @testsetup exist in test class how do you call this method data from the testmethod.
A. No need to class separately, The data will be available for the all test methods. If a test class contains a test setup method, the testing framework executes the test setup method first, before any test method in the class. Records that are created in a test setup method are available to all test methods in the test class and are rolled back at the end of test class executionss 

Q. What is the difference between testMethod and @isTest in Salesforce?
A. While creating a Test Method both act same, but @isTest is the enhanced version of 'TestMethod' keyword. In case of best practice, we always use @isTest annotation for creating a Test method.

