A.Copy code from to sandbox and replicate the issue in sandbox and use system.debug statements to analyze the issue.
Q. what are the primitive and non-primitive data types in SF?
A. The non primitive data types in salesforce are the sobjects such as Standard objects and custom objects.
QA. I have workflow rule to update contact amount 600 but on the contact we have a validation rule that if amount greater than to 500 through error. Now what will happen whether field will get update or error will through.
A. Field will get update with 600 because, If the record was updated with workflow field updates, fires before update triggers and after update triggers one more time (and only one more time), in addition to standard validations will execute. Custom validation rules, flows, duplicate rules, processes, and escalation rules are not run again.

